87422542,Research and Data Analyst,Hays | Executive,https://www.seek.com.au/job/87422542?type=standard&ref=search-standalone&origin=jobCard#sol=37c50d570dd72990f0940d867c7794317ce27ed8,1h ago,1.0,2025-09-24T06:00:00+00:00,Sydney NSW (Hybrid),Teaching - Vocational (Education & Training),Full time,,"Your new company

Service and Creative Skills Australia (SaCSA) is an industry-owned, industry-led Jobs & Skills Council (JSC) funded by the Department of Employment & Workplace Relations (DEWR). We partner with industry, unions and government across the Arts, Personal Services, Retail, Tourism and Hospitality sectors to identify current and future employment trends and develop solutions that deliver better outcomes for employers, workers, learners, trainers, and educators.
The successful candidate can be based in Sydney, Canberra or Melbourne.
Your new role
Lead and conduct applied research on workforce trends, emerging occupations, and training needs.
Analyse and interpret labour-market and training data (e.g., ABS, NCVER, JSA), integrating stakeholder insights into clear recommendations.
Generate high-quality reports and briefings that communicate findings to varied audiences across government and industry.
Oversee and project-manage research and reporting workflows, contributing to multiple concurrent projects from scoping to evaluation.
Inform workforce plans and sector updates, including deep dives into key occupations/segments.
Liaise with industry experts and research organisations to capture new evidence and emerging trends.
Collaborate across SaCSA to embed insights into program and product design.
What you'll need to succeed
Tertiary qualifications or equivalent experience in Economics, Policy Research, or a related discipline.
Demonstrated experience with economic and labour-market topics within national/state policy contexts.
Proven research, analysis, and report-writing skills, communicating to senior (and junior) audiences.
Proficiency in analytical and visualisation tools such as Excel, Python/R, SPSS, Power BI, Tableau, or similar platforms
Project management capability and comfort balancing multiple priorities.
Strong stakeholder engagement skills: VET sector networks and experience engaging with VET policy (e.g., education/training departments, regulators) are desirable.
What you'll get in return
Influence the direction of Australia's skills system across dynamic, creative, and service-oriented industries.
Join a collaborative, inclusive team committed to continuous improvement and evidence-based decision-making.
Opportunities for professional development and work with national impact.
What you need to do now
Please submit your CV and a brief cover letter outlining your alignment to the role's requirements.
Confidential enquiries:
Andy Sundberg, Hays Executive
E: Andy.Sundberg@hays.com.au
If you're interested in this role, click 'apply now' to forward an up-to-date copy of your CV, or call us now.
If this job isn't quite right for you, but you are looking for a new position, please contact us for a confidential discussion about your career."

87422460,Data Engineer,HorizonOne Recruitment,https://www.seek.com.au/job/87422460?type=standard&ref=search-standalone&origin=jobCard#sol=e6b726993ef8bebc2c62004983623136398f88c2,1h ago,1.0,2025-09-24T06:00:00+00:00,Canberra ACT,Government - Federal (Government & Defence),Full time,$125/hr - $150/hr,"This role is within a large social policy agency where we're partnering with the Director on a project to assess the financial and economic impact of cutting regulatory red tape.
This regulatory alignment had been approved for development through a previous MYEFO measure.
The Opportunity
This is a rare opportunity to join a high-calibre team at the start of a major reform program.
You will play a key part in shaping the data for a model that underpins national policy advice and budget decisions.
With funding approved from the Deputy Secretary until June 2026 and strong prospects for extension, this role offers:
A close knit outcomes driven team with a friendly and technical EL2 who believes in gold standard work but is but is pragmatic enough to be able to build models based on assumptions
A clear line of sight of the work you’re doing with initial results due for next year’s budget
A meaningful contribution to reforms improving outcomes for vulnerable Australians
You will be joining a four person tiger team that will hit the ground running to produce an impact assessment report for next year’s budget
The economic model has already been developed in-house by the Director, incorporating Cost–Benefit Analysis and CGE modelling.
The Role
Your work helps answer questions like “If incomes changes, how do travel or service choices shift?"" The data you prepare underpins economic scenarios across multiple service lines.
As the Data Engineer, you will:
Clean and structure large datasets
Build pipelines and data-matching models for forward-looking, timeseries analysis
Enable the team to run 5-year cost-benefit modelling that informs national reform
The Ideal Person
This role will suit a data engineer, scientist, or analyst who
Is highly skilled in R or Python for cleaning, wrangling, and integrating large datasets
Experienced working with policy/ program teams to understand the types of questions they will ask

Bonus points if you have an economic background or experience and have worked at agencies including DEWR, JSA, Treasury, Department of Health, Disability and Ageing, DSS, NDIA directly or via consulting
Due to the nature of the work Australian Citizenship and existing Baseline clearance is mandatory.
Salary / Rate
EL1 equivalent labour hire contract October – 30/6/26 with likely extensions
A guide for the rate is $120/hr - $150/hr including Super or + GST
How to Apply
To apply online, please click on the appropriate link.
Alternatively, for a confidential discussion, please contact Lucas Walker on 0483 911 561 quoting ref no. 20987
HorizonOne is committed to building a diverse and inclusive workforce and we encourage applications from people of all cultures, capabilities and backgrounds."

87421655,Senior Change Manager - Major Data Transformation,The Aquarium,https://www.seek.com.au/job/87421655?type=standard&ref=search-standalone&origin=jobCard#sol=ee4d4818bff247bd15b90620b522ce5b9791200a,1h ago,1.0,2025-09-24T06:00:00+00:00,Sydney NSW (Hybrid),Management & Change Consulting (Consulting & Strategy),Contract/Temp,Up to $1100 p/d + GST - 3 Yr Program,"Senior Change Lead – Data & AI Transformation
Sydney CBD | 6-Month Rolling Contract | $1100 p/d + GST

Our customer is delivering one of Australia’s most significant transformation programs—a multi-year initiative to embed data and AI at the heart of business decision-making. This is a career-defining opportunity to take a senior leadership role in a program that blends advanced technology with enterprise-wide organisational change.
The Role
As Senior Change Lead, you’ll be accountable for shaping and executing the change strategy across this complex transformation. This includes:
Owning the change agenda – leading impact assessments, readiness plans, and transition roadmaps to embed change at scale.
Executive & stakeholder engagement – influencing C-suite leaders and engaging cross-functional teams to ensure alignment.
Cultural & behavioural adoption – championing new ways of working, role-based access, and data-driven practices.
Capability uplift – designing and delivering persona-based training and enablement to build sustainable skills.
Risk & governance oversight – managing dependencies, mitigating people-related risks, and embedding governance structures within Agile delivery.
About You
We’re seeking a proven Senior Change Manager / Lead who has delivered complex, large-scale technology transformations. To succeed, you’ll bring:
10+ years’ experience in leading organisational change at senior levels.
A track record of delivering change in enterprise technology, digital, or data programs with budgets in the tens of millions.
Proven ability to operate at executive level – influencing C-suite stakeholders while ensuring adoption at the frontline.
Expertise in Agile, Lean, and project management frameworks (e.g. PRINCE2, PMP).
Strong risk management and business readiness skills, including handling ambiguity and resistance.
Exceptional communication, coaching, and leadership capabilities.
Why This Role?
Lead change on a flagship transformation with national visibility.
Drive adoption of cutting-edge data and AI capabilities.
Rolling 6-month contract with strong extension potential.
Competitive daily rate: $1100 + GST.
Please reach out to the team at The Aquarium for more information.
www.TheAquarium.com.au"

87421498,"Senior Analyst, Internal Audit",AustralianSuper,https://www.seek.com.au/job/87421498?type=standard&ref=search-standalone&origin=jobCard#sol=b21d5a80a8518baa3980c3a5a2a6b92b93e790f7,1h ago,1.0,2025-09-24T06:00:00+00:00,Melbourne VIC (Hybrid),Compliance & Risk (Banking & Financial Services),Full time,,"At AustralianSuper, we truly care about our colleagues. We know work and life are intertwined. That's why we support the diverse needs of everyone and have policies that enable us all to thrive and be truly flexible. We ensure diversity is celebrated for the opportunity it provides us all to learn and grow and deliver better outcomes for members. We are dedicated to building a high-performance environment underpinned by a strong risk culture, ensuring we deliver the best outcomes for our members.
Your New Role

The Internal Audit team's function is to enhance and protect organisational value by providing risk-based and objective assurance, advice, and insight. This is achieved by providing an independent, objective assurance and advisory service designed to add value and improve operations through evaluating and improving effectiveness of risk management, control and governance processes.

In this role you will be re porting to the Principal, Internal Audit. As a Senior Analyst, you are a key member of the expanding AustralianSuper global Internal Audit team and will play a key role in delivering core elements of the annual Global Internal Audit Plan.
Key duties include but not limited to
Working with the Chief Audit Executive to establish a 'world class' global Internal Audit function
Supporting the Principal, Internal Audit in their duties and reporting to the Chief Audit Executive
Assisting the Global Internal Audit team perform a range of internal audit services targeted to the Fund's operations and risks
Assist the team with performing internal audit work in line with the Global Internal Audit Methodology Standard including planning, scoping, fieldwork, reporting and stakeholder management
Taking accountability for various Internal Audit management activities and uplift initiatives
Promote Internal Audit and learn the business by attending various forums led by Line 1 and Line 2 risk colleagues to keep up to date with initiatives within their teams.
What You'll Need
At least 3 years of experience in internal/external audit, accounting, risk or related discipline
Certified Internal Auditor (CIA) or Certified Information System Auditor (CISA) qualifications or commitment to attain either designation required
Financial Services or Superannuation experience essential
Chartered Accountant (CA) qualification highly regarded
Ability to analyse data to determine the extent of adherence to policy, procedure and process
Previous experience with a business governance, risk and control (GRC) system highly regarded
Well developed written and verbal influencing skills
Curiosity to acquire and develop business acumen
Ability to work effectively and independently
Ambition to drive your own continuous professional development.
Life at AustralianSuper

AustralianSuper is committed to colleague development, and we support our people with ongoing learning, coaching and training, as well as career opportunities across our expanding global organisation. We offer generous leave entitlements and promote a blended working environment in which all roles can flex, and we're happy to discuss what this looks like for you.

We cultivate a workplace that champions safety, respect, inclusiveness and diversity. We are committed to supporting our diverse workforce in a way that is inclusive and embraces diversity in all its forms. If you require any reasonable adjustments to the recruitment process or the role, please let our recruitment team know.
What's Next

Apply now, if you share our values of Energy, Integrity, Generosity of Spirit and Excellent Outcomes and would like the opportunity to work in a challenging, growing and rapidly evolving team to deliver outstanding results.
Australian or New Zealand citizenship or Australian permanent residency status is required.
Progress powered by purpose.

Agencies please note: this vacancy is being managed directly by AustralianSuper's Talent Acquisition team. We will contact our preferred agency partners should we require additional support. Thank you."

87423378,Senior Director - Client Advisory - Consulting & Analytics,Visa,https://www.seek.com.au/job/87423378?type=standard&ref=search-standalone&origin=jobCard#sol=6ef0739cda454681d9c141ecd7aa7fb4ab311f47,2h ago,2.0,2025-09-24T05:00:00+00:00,Sydney NSW (Hybrid),Management & Change Consulting (Consulting & Strategy),Full time,,"Company Description

Visa is a world leader in payments and technology, with over 259 billion payments transactions flowing safely between consumers, merchants, financial institutions, and government entities in more than 200 countries and territories each year. Our mission is to connect the world through the most innovative, convenient, reliable, and secure payments network, enabling individuals, businesses, and economies to thrive while driven by a common purpose – to uplift everyone, everywhere by being the best way to pay and be paid.
Make an impact with a purpose-driven industry leader. Join us today and experience Life at Visa.
Job Description
Team Summary

Visa Consulting & Analytics (VCA) is Visa's consulting division, serving Visa's clients (including card issuers, acquirers, and merchants) and solving their strategic problems focused on improving performance and profitability.  Drawing on our expertise in strategy consulting, payments, data analytics, marketing, operational and macroeconomics, VCA drives high impact and tangible financial results.

The C&A team within Australia provides a comprehensive range of consulting services and solutions to our clients in Australia and New Zealand, that address unique challenges in areas such as strategic growth, profitability, risk management and digital strategy.
What a Senior Director, Client Advisory Australia does at Visa:

The Head of Client Advisory Australia, a Senior Director within Visa Consulting & Analytics, leads the strategic direction and delivery of the Client Advisory function across the Australian market. As the team leader, this role is responsible for accelerating business growth and driving the success of VCA’s consulting, managed services, data services, and advisory offerings.

Overseeing a high-performing team, the Senior Director identifies and pursues new business opportunities, fosters trusted relationships with executive-level clients, and ensures the consistent delivery of high-impact engagements that enable clients to achieve portfolio growth and enhanced profitability. The Head of Client Advisory Australia sets the vision for the team, orchestrates complex consulting projects from inception to execution, and represents VCA in both internal forums and the broader financial services ecosystem.
Responsibilities
The Senior Director, Client Advisory Australia will:

Build executive client relationships - The Head of Client Advisory is responsible for cultivating and maintaining robust executive-level relationships across the Australian financial services industry. By establishing trust and thought leadership, they serve as the primary point of contact for senior stakeholders, enabling Visa to deeply understand client objectives and position itself as a preferred advisor.

Overseeing and pitching high-quality proposals - This leader oversees the end-to-end process of preparing, tailoring, and presenting compelling project proposals to clients. By clarifying project objectives, scope, deliverables, and approach, they ensure that proposals not only meet client needs but also position Visa’s expertise and unique value proposition, leading to the successful sale and initiation of major programs of work.

Leveraging Consulting, Data Science, and Implementation Teams - The Head of Client Advisory harnesses the full breadth of Visa’s consulting, data science, and implementation resources to deliver best-in-class solutions. By collaborating with multidisciplinary teams, they orchestrate the design and execution of innovative strategies, using data-driven insights and operational expertise to drive measurable client outcomes.

Achieving sales and revenue targets - A key measure of success for this role is the achievement of sales and revenue goals for the Australian market. The Head of Client Advisory leads business development efforts, identifying new opportunities, writing proposals, scoping projects, and ensuring a strong pipeline of engagements that accelerate Visa Consulting & Analytics’ growth ambitions.

Leading and motivating the Client Advisory Team - Managing a team of 6-7 full-time employees (FTE), the Head of Client Advisory fosters a high-performance culture, providing clear direction, support, and professional development for team members. Effective leadership ensures that the team remains motivated, engaged, and equipped to deliver to the highest standards.

Representing the business internally and externally - Serving as the voice of Client Advisory, this role not only represents the function within Visa—collaborating with senior management and cross-functional colleagues—but also externally, acting as an ambassador for VCA at industry events, in client forums, and across the broader financial services ecosystem.

Ensuring high-quality project delivery and direct client engagement - This leader is accountable for the delivery of high-quality, impactful project outcomes. They oversee project setup, stakeholder engagement, data analysis, benchmarking, and diagnostics. Importantly, they are personally involved in key client meetings, ensuring that recommendations are well communicated and that execution aligns with client expectations and Visa’s standards of excellence.
Qualifications

Having already accumulated a variety of experience, you will be familiar with the payments industry and keen to work alongside an experienced team in gaining a deeper understanding. You will be client driven, comfortable managing a project end to end and relishing the opportunity to work closely with clients to influence their future performance.
Specific skills and experience you will bring are:
15+ years of deep experience in consulting, corporate strategy, or business management with a Bachelor’s Degree
Deep experience in managing complex projects and simultaneously managing multiple projects
Superior analytical and problem-solving skills, with demonstrated intellectual and analytical rigour
Strong team orientation with a collaborative, diplomatic, and flexible style, able to work effectively in a matrixed organisation
Excellent detail orientation, ensuring the highest level of quality/rigour in reports and data analysis
Excellent presentation skills, including strong oral and written capabilities
Self-motivated, results-oriented individual with the ability to progress multiple priorities concurrently
Experience in and passion for the power of analytics to inform and drive strategy and tactics, and proven ability to generate insights from data
Strong commercial acumen, with experience in working on business/value cases that prove ROI
In addition, you will ideally bring the following:
Experience in payments or retail banking industry
Experience in developing strategy (for products or business units)
Experience in customer experience design (using human centred design / design thinking)
An understanding of statistical analysis, modelling, scoring schemes, etc.
Additional Information

This is a hybrid position, based in Sydney or Melbourne, Australia. Employees in hybrid roles are required to work from the Sydney office on Tuesdays, Wednesdays, and Thursdays of each week, based on business needs.
Additional Information

Visa is an EEO Employer. Qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity, disability or protected veteran status. Visa will also consider for employment qualified applicants with criminal histories in a manner consistent with EEOC guidelines and applicable local law."

2–5+ years of experience in data analytics, data science, or a related role
Strong proficiency in SQL and database systems
Experience with data visualization tools such as Tableau, Power BI, Cognos, or Looker
Familiarity with cloud platforms such as AWS, GCP, or Azure
Experience or knowledge of AI technologies such as Large Language Models (LLMs), Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG), or agent-based systems
Want to know more? apply now!
At Compare the Market and iSelect and we’re proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer and we embrace diversity.

Compare the Market and iSelect are committed to protecting your privacy. Sportsbet is seeking a Senior Value Analyst to join our dynamic Customer Generosity team. This role is pivotal in driving the design, implementation, and evaluation of our industry-leading Customer Generosity Program,  delivering value to both customers and the business.

87410144,Senior Supervisor/Lawyer/Analyst,ASIC,https://www.seek.com.au/job/87410144?type=standard&ref=search-standalone&origin=jobCard#sol=de79372471aea59bb910acbb0807f93887123636,7h ago,7.0,2025-09-24T00:00:00+00:00,Melbourne VIC (Hybrid),Government - Federal (Government & Defence),Full time,,"At ASIC, you can be the change that ensures a fair, strong and efficient financial system for the benefit of all Australians. Implement best practice surveillance and supervision to achieve robust and impactful regulatory outcomes. Seeking an expert in complex, risk-based surveillance and supervision with exceptional stakeholder relationship skills.
All locations considered
Permanent position
Salary from $152,074 + 15.4% superannuation
Applications close at 11:59pm AEDT, 9 October 2025.
The team

The Strategic Surveillance, Banking and Data (SSBD) team delivers proactive surveillance outcomes across multiple sectors using thematic surveillance expertise, running complex surveillances within and across sectors and leading group wide activities.

SSBD is responsible for the regulation and supervision of the banking sector and strategically important financial institutions. This includes proactive engagement with and monitoring of firms to understand and respond to emerging industry issues and provide strategic direction and technical expertise for ASIC's work.

The team collaborates with other parts of ASIC in ensuring consistent and effective delivery of ASIC's regulatory priorities by using best practice regulatory supervision, surveillance knowledge, expertise, and resources on Regulation & Supervision (R&S) or ASIC wide projects.
The role
As a Senior Analyst/Lawyer/Supervisor you will be responsible for:
Making significant contributions to the delivery of complex data driven surveillances and ASIC wide or priority projects.

Making significant and strategic contributions to the supervision of the banking sector including identification of and addressing emerging and current risks, stakeholder engagement and assessing applications to exercise discretionary powers.
Developing and maintaining key internal and external relationships with stakeholders, including representing ASIC at government or industry meetings

Leading and identifying new ways to utilise data to deliver priorities and support evidence based decision making, including effective collection, management, analysis, and communication of insights from data.
Contributing to the guidance, training, direction and mentoring of junior team members.
Maintaining knowledge of ASIC's regulatory framework and toolkit, relevant legislative and reporting requirements, domestic and international developments, and best industry practice models.
About you

You will possess a strong understanding of the benefits of strategic relationships to maximise data and information opportunities, with experience in advising on complex transactions or projects requiring critical thinking and judgment in relevant industries such as legal firms, or regulatory environments.
You will also demonstrate:
Relevant tertiary qualification.
Deep knowledge of banking, Australian financial markets, and the regulatory environment.
Strong strategic thinking, analytical, investigative, and research skills.
Proven ability to develop strategic relationships for effective data use.
Experience leading high-performing teams with a focus on strategic direction and coaching.
Excellent communication skills and attention to detail in business reporting.
About ASIC

ASIC's remit is one of the broadest of regulators across the world. ASIC regulates corporations, markets, financial services and consumer credit and monitors and promotes market integrity and consumer protection in the Australian financial system. Through our enforcement work, we hold to account those who contravene the law, working to achieve strong outcomes that address the greatest consumer and investor harms.

ASIC is committed to a providing a diverse and inclusive workplace where the very best talent in Australia chooses to work. Indigenous Australians are encouraged to apply as well as applicants from all backgrounds and with different abilities.
We offer a range of employee benefits including:
Attractive superannuation
Additional leave entitlements
50/50 hybrid work-from home model
Flexible work arrangements
Assistance for study and professional development
Click here to view ASIC's salary and benefits guide.
To read more about ASIC, you can visit our website or review our Corporate Plan.
To work with us, you need to be an Australian citizen and be prepared to complete an ASIC Suitability and Baseline Assessment.
View the position description for more information or click ‘apply' to start your application. Applications close at 11:59pm AEDT, 9 October 2025."
